messages.text: They want me to become a member?
Yes. They think you have a lot of potential.
They love that you want to be a Supreme Court Justice. They‚Äôll make that dream a reality.
Why? What do they get in return?
Think of the Source like a network at a country club.
Everyone helps each other out in the hope that the rest of the members will benefit.
So, it‚Äôs like a nepotism thing?
No, it‚Äôs like a supportive community thing.
Sorry, but it sounds shady.
Who‚Äôs in this ‚Äúsecret society?‚Äù
And how can they guarantee anything?
Lots of influential people.
Politicians, businessmen, lawyers, doctors‚Äî
Even some celebrities.
That still doesn‚Äôt explain why they think they can just MAKE me a Supreme Court Justice.
Not sure if you‚Äôre aware, but it‚Äôs a super hard thing to accomplish.
Look, you can‚Äôt repeat this to anyone‚Ä¶
But the Source has been practically running our entire government since the early 1900s.
That‚Äôs when my grandpa got in, back when he was a senator.
My family‚Äôs been a part of it ever since.
Kyle, this is a lot to take in. Can we back up?
What if I don‚Äôt want an abortion?
They‚Äôve made it very clear that if I want to be president someday‚Ä¶
And if you want to be a Supreme Court Justice‚Ä¶
We can‚Äôt have a baby this young.
It‚Äôd completely change the way people would look at us politically.
No one would take us seriously.
What if I don‚Äôt care how people look at me?
Angie, please. You totally do. Besides‚Äî
You‚Äôd have to put all of your dreams on hold to have this baby.
You wouldn‚Äôt be able to go to college, let alone law school, for years‚Äî
If you ever go at all.
And that‚Äôs assuming your parents won‚Äôt cut you off financially.
Chances are you wouldn‚Äôt be able to swing the tuition.
I didn‚Äôt think of that‚Ä¶
Well, I can‚Äôt stop thinking about it.
Let‚Äôs say you did go to college at some point.
You‚Äôd have to raise our kid and hold down a steady job to support it‚Äî
So you‚Äôd have to go to school part-time. It‚Äôd be exhausting.
And you‚Äôd be setting yourself back by decades, at least.
You mean *we‚Äôd* be setting ourselves back by decades.
Or are you not as ‚Äúin this with me‚Äù as you say you are?
Angie, don‚Äôt be mad. You know that‚Äôs what I meant.
I‚Äôm just trying to make you see that this decision has huge consequences.
I don‚Äôt want you to make it lightly.
Especially since you‚Äôve worked so hard to maintain a 4.0 GPA and score almost-perfect SAT scores.
AND you landed that summer internship at that law firm‚Ä¶
I know.
Well, just know they won‚Äôt be happy with their ONE high school intern if she shows up pregnant.
At that point, it wouldn‚Äôt even matter that she‚Äôs the daughter of the President.
I know this may sound harsh, but I‚Äôm just trying to warn you‚Ä¶
That‚Äôs not exactly the image they‚Äôll want for their firm.
I know. You‚Äôre right.
So if I accepted the invitation from the Source‚Ä¶
What would I have to do as a member?
Is there like‚Ä¶a monthly meeting or something?
No, nothing like that.
Members rarely meet up in large group settings.
It‚Äôs usually more one-on-one, for business purposes.
So‚Ä¶I‚Äôd just be a member, and they‚Äôd help me become a Supreme Court Justice?
They do ask for favors from time to time.
It‚Äôs one of those ‚Äúyou scratch my back, I scratch yours‚Äù kind of organizations.
What kind of favors?
They‚Äôll text you with more details.
Just promise me you won‚Äôt shut them down right away.
You haven‚Äôt been initiated yet, so you‚Äôre not committed to anything.
I just don‚Äôt want you to close the door on your future before you consider all of your options.
Fine. I‚Äôll hear them out.
At 9 am the next morning, Angie receives a text.
Good morning, Angie.
We trust Mr. Whitfield let you know we would be contacting you.
Is this the Source?
I‚Äôm sure Mr. Whitfield explained that we ask all of our applicants to complete small tasks during the initiation process.
Your willingness to accomplish these tasks allows us to judge your loyalty.
Your ability to accomplish the tasks allows us to judge your ingenuity.
Are you ready for your first task?
Angie hesitates, then remembers the promise she made to Kyle.
She won‚Äôt close the door on their future just yet.
Yes.
We have been informed that Mr. Whitfield will be your date to the charity ball this evening.
Senator Lynthrop is also going to be in attendance.
We would like for you to flirt with the senator in a private, discreet location.
Mr. Whitfield already has an area in mind.
Mr. Whitfield will take photographic evidence of the encounter. He will then send it to us.
But Senator Lynthrop is in his 50‚Äôs.
And he‚Äôs married.
Why would you want to get pictures of him flirting with me?
Recruitment.
